OL,3,CCourts will sit for extra days to
OL,4,Ctackle growing backlog
OL,6,FPeer and reality television star Lord
OL,7,FCharles Brocket, who appeared before
OL,8,FIsleworth Crown Court on Tuesday
OL,9,Ffacing allegations of sexual assault
OL,10,Fand rape, was told his trial would not
OL,11,Fbe heard until November 2027.
OL,13,FDuring the hearing, the Recorder of
OL,14,Fthe Royal Borough of Kensington, Judge
OL,15,FMartin Edmunds KC, issued an apology
OL,16,F"to all concerned" for the delay. No
OL,17,Fpleas were entered in the hearing.
